### Current Progress
- Discovered and documented severe bottlenecks in the middleware stack.
- Refactored `ExtractTokenMiddleware` to process JWTs early and avoid quadruple parsing.
- Refactored `ArmedMiddleware` to use a 2-second in-memory cache, eliminating per-request `os.ReadDir` overhead.
- Implemented an LRU cache (`lruCache`) in `ip_hopping.go` to fix unbounded memory growth of `lastIPs`.
- Made `triggerMFA` asynchronously write to the DB, preventing rate-limiter logic from blocking DB connections.
- Removed global `penaltyBox` variables from `middleware.go`, making rate limiters stateless instances.
- Re-ran tests with `JWT_SECRET=test-secret go test ./internal/middleware` and `go test ./...`. All tests pass.

### Next Steps
- None. This plan is fully complete and verified.
